OL,6,FAhead of the debate, shadow work and
OL,7,Fpensions secretary Helen Whately said:
OL,8,F"Labour are unleashing a #14 billion
OL,9,Fbenefits spending spree. Worse, this
OL,10,Fshovels nearly half the cash to
OL,11,Fjobless households with average
OL,12,Fpayouts of #25,000.
OL,14,F"Work is being punished while
OL,15,Fworklessness is rewarded. Keir Starmer
OL,16,Fwas happy to take money away from
OL,17,Fpensioners, but he doesn't have the
OL,18,Fbackbone to say no to his own MPs when
OL,19,Fthey demand runaway welfare spending.
