OL,6,F"Labour and Reform both want to blow
OL,7,Fthe cap. Only the Conservatives are
OL,8,Fwilling to say no, restore discipline
OL,9,Fto welfare, support work, and protect
OL,10,Ftaxpayers."
OL,12,FThe Office for Budget Responsibility
OL,13,F(OBR) said the move will cost #3
OL,14,Fbillion a year by 2029/30.
OL,16,FWork and Pensions Secretary Pat
OL,17,FMcFadden has previously said lifting
OL,18,Fthe two-child benefit cap is an
OL,19,F"investment" in the future.
